        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-238",
        "content": "Only those who have heard Jane sing THE ROSARY can possibly realise how she sang \"I KISS EACH BEAD.\" The lingering retrospection in each word; breathed out a love so womanly, so beautiful, so tender, that her identity was forgotten-even by those in the audience who knew her best-in the magic of her rendering of the song.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-normal_e-low",
        "gender": "F",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
